<li><i>The Sun, The Genome and The Internet</i>, 1999. <a href="http://www.sfsite.com/08b/sun63.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.sfsite.com/08b/sun63.htm" rel="nofollow">Review</a></li>
<li><i>L'mportanza di essere imprevedibile</i>, Di Renzo Editore, 2003</li>
<li><i><a href="/wiki/The_Scientist_as_Rebel" title="The Scientist as Rebel">The Scientist as Rebel</a></i>, 2006. <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2007/01/07/books/review/Johnson.t.html" class="external text" title="http://www.nytimes.com/2007/01/07/books/review/Johnson.t.html" rel="nofollow">Review</a></li>
<li><i>Advanced Quantum Mechanics</i>, World Scientific, 2007. Dyson's 1951 Cornell lecture notes transcribed by David Derbes.</li>
<li><i>A Many-Colored Glass: Reflections on the Place of Life in the Universe</i>, University of Virginia Press, 2007. <a href="http://brneurosci.org/reviews/dyson.html" class="external text" title="http://brneurosci.org/reviews/dyson.html" rel="nofollow">Review</a></li>
</ul>
