<h4><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Freeman_Dyson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=27" title="Edit section: About Dyson">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">About Dyson</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2009/03/29/magazine/29Dyson-t.html?sq=Freeman" class="external text" title="http://www.nytimes.com/2009/03/29/magazine/29Dyson-t.html?sq=Freeman" rel="nofollow">"The Civil Heretic "</a>, profile at the <i><a href="/wiki/New_York_Times_Magazine" title="New York Times Magazine" class="mw-redirect">New York Times Magazine</a></i> by <a href="/wiki/Nicholas_Dawidoff" title="Nicholas Dawidoff">Nicholas Dawidoff</a>, March 25, 2009</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFO.27ConnorRobertson"><a href="/wiki/John_J._O%27Connor_(mathematician)" title="John J. O'Connor (mathematician)" class="mw-redirect">O'Connor, John J.</a>; <a href="/wiki/Edmund_F._Robertson" title="Edmund F. Robertson">Robertson, Edmund F.</a>, <a href="http://www-history.mcs.st-andrews.ac.uk/Biographies/Dyson.html" class="external text" title="http://www-history.mcs.st-andrews.ac.uk/Biographies/Dyson.html" rel="nofollow">"Freeman Dyson"</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/MacTutor_History_of_Mathematics_archive" title="MacTutor History of Mathematics archive">MacTutor History of Mathematics archive</a></i></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Freeman+Dyson&amp;rft.atitle=%5B%5BMacTutor+History+of+Mathematics+archive%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=O%27Connor&amp;rft.aufirst=John+J.&amp;rft.au=O%27Connor%2C+John+J.&amp;rft.au=Robertson%2C+Edmund+F.&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Freeman_Dyson"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>, biography, circa 2000</li>
<li><a href="http://www.sns.ias.edu/~dyson/longbio.html" class="external text" title="http://www.sns.ias.edu/~dyson/longbio.html" rel="nofollow">Dyson biographical outline</a>, circa 2005</li>
<li><a href="http://www.nybooks.com/authors/514" class="external text" title="http://www.nybooks.com/authors/514" rel="nofollow">Dyson author page and archive</a>, from <i><a href="/wiki/The_New_York_Review_of_Books" title="The New York Review of Books">The New York Review of Books</a></i></li>
<li><a href="http://www.wildriverreview.com/quarkpark_dyson.php" class="external text" title="http://www.wildriverreview.com/quarkpark_dyson.php" rel="nofollow">"The Scientist as Rebel"</a>, 2005 interview at <i><a href="/wiki/Wild_River_Review" title="Wild River Review">Wild River Review</a></i></li>
<li><a href="http://www.npr.org/rundowns/segment.php?wfId=4139566" class="external text" title="http://www.npr.org/rundowns/segment.php?wfId=4139566" rel="nofollow">NPR interview of Freeman Dyson</a>, audio, <i><a href="/wiki/All_Things_Considered" title="All Things Considered">All Things Considered</a></i>, November 2, 2004</li>
<li><a href="http://video.google.com/videoplay?docid=350379535220823176&amp;q=genome" class="external text" title="http://video.google.com/videoplay?docid=350379535220823176&amp;q=genome" rel="nofollow">Google video: interviewer: Robert Wright</a>, video, 44:55, June 30, 2001</li>
<li><a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/sci/tech/740688.stm" class="external text" title="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/sci/tech/740688.stm" rel="nofollow">Freeman Dyson wins $1m religion prize</a>, 9 May 2000</li>
<li><a href="http://www.wired.com/wired/archive/6.02/dyson.html" class="external text" title="http://www.wired.com/wired/archive/6.02/dyson.html" rel="nofollow">"Freeman Dyson's Brain"</a>, interview by <a href="/wiki/Stewart_Brand" title="Stewart Brand">Stewart Brand</a> at <i><a href="/wiki/Wired_(magazine)" title="Wired (magazine)">Wired</a></i>, 1998</li>
<li><a href="http://www.aip.org/history/ohilist/4585.html" class="external text" title="http://www.aip.org/history/ohilist/4585.html" rel="nofollow">Oral History interview transcript with Freeman J. Dyson 17 December 1986</a>, <a href="/wiki/American_Institute_of_Physics" title="American Institute of Physics">American Institute of Physics</a>, Niels Bohr Library and Archives</li>
